This paper focuses on measuring the transport difficulty for content dissemination in online social networks (OSNs), which involves network infrastructure, social behavior, and content distribution. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also discusses the geographical distribution feature of dissemination sessions in OSNs, which relates to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also introduces a new session pattern, which is related to cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
